To make this work there&#39;s two options. The first one here is my preferred

**Option 1**

Push a new object instead of a reference to an object already in data. So this would look like

```js
async addUserToSelection(){
  let user = Object.assign({},this.users.availableUsers.find(u =&gt; u.login === this.users.selected),{
    admin: false,
    creator: false,
    responsible: false
  });
  if(!this.userExistsInPermissionTable(user) &amp;&amp; user._id){        
    try {        
      await addUserPermission(user);
      this.permissionTable.users.push(user);
    } catch (err) {
      console.log(err);
    }
  }     
}
```

**Option 2**

Set the new Keys using the vm.$set method (I&#39;m just showing what&#39;s different to Option 1)

```js
let user = this.users.availableUsers.find(u =&gt; u.login === this.users.selected)
