It is stated that Vuetify v-select does not have an input value. Longer answer by Vuetify dev [here][1]. They are just not setting the value to input.

The solution would be to add a hidden input that keeps the selected value and is submitted with form.

Example [codepen][2]

&lt;!-- begin snippet: js hide: false console: true babel: false --&gt;

&lt;!-- language: lang-js --&gt;

    new Vue({
      el: &#39;#app&#39;,
      vuetify: new Vuetify(),
      data: () =&gt; ({
        subjects: [&#39;Subject1&#39;, &#39;Subject2&#39;, &#39;Subject3&#39;, &#39;Subject4&#39;],
        selectedSubject: &#39;&#39;
      }),
    })

&lt;!-- language: lang-html --&gt;

    &lt;div id=&quot;app&quot;&gt;
      &lt;v-app id=&quot;inspire&quot;&gt;
        &lt;v-container fluid&gt;
          &lt;v-row align=&quot;center&quot;&gt;
            &lt;v-col class=&quot;d-flex&quot; cols=&quot;12&quot; sm=&quot;6&quot;&gt;
              &lt;v-select
                v-model=&quot;selectedSubject&quot;
                :items=&quot;subjects&quot;
                label=&quot;Subjects&quot;
                solo
              &gt;&lt;/v-select&gt;
              &lt;input type=&quot;hidden&quot; v-model=&quot;selectedSubject&quot; name=&quot;subject&quot;&gt;
            &lt;/v-col&gt;
          &lt;/v-row&gt;
        &lt;/v-container&gt;
      &lt;/v-app&gt;
    &lt;/div&gt;

&lt;!-- end snippet --&gt;

